{{no footnotes|date=June 2016 }}
'''Cyphonism''' ([[Greek language|Gr]] {{Lang|el|κυφωνισμός}}, from {{Lang|el|κῡφός}}, "bent, crooked") was a form of punishment by the {{Lang|el|κύφων}} (''kyphon''), a sort of wooden [[pillory]] by which the neck of the malefactor was bent or weighed downward. Formerly, this term was widely believed to refer to a form of punishment in which the criminal's naked body was smeared with honey, and exposed him to flies, wasps, etc.

