'''Joan Bernard Armstrong''' ({{circa|1941}} – June 9, 2018) was an African-American judge

Armstrong was "the first woman elected to serve as a judge in Louisiana and first African-American to serve as chief judge of the state's Fourth [[Louisiana Circuit Courts of Appeals|Circuit Courts of Appeal]]."<ref>[https://www.nola.com/politics/index.ssf/2018/06/joan_bernard_armstrong_dead.html Joan Bernard Armstrong, 1st female judge in Louisiana, dies at 77]</ref>

